Themes like the Documentation theme and the Default theme support customized layouts.  For other themes (such as the Left Navigation theme and Clickr theme), when you access the "Layouts" tool in the site or space admin panel, a message like the following appears:

{quote}
You can not customise the site look and feel while a theme is active. You must first disable currently configured theme.
{quote}

The Default and Documentation theme will both respect custom layouts regardless of which theme you enter them in.  The older themes don't respect custom layouts.

It would be better to display a message like "This theme doesn't support layouts" instead.

