I have the following wiki code in my pages:

{code}
&nbsp;!Icons^d.png!!Icons^t.png!!Icons^p.png!
{code}

This works fine confluence 2.9 (it shows a blank and 3 images)
But in 3.1 this is broken: [See it here|^Picture 1.png]

It works when I add a space after &nbsp;
{code}
&nbsp; !Icons^d.png!!Icons^t.png!!Icons^p.png!
{code}


So the first image is not rendered correctly, it seems like the preceding &nbsp; is breaking the recognition of the image... This bug is problematic because this code is contained in lots of pages....

I've only been able to replicate this in IE 8, and it's pretty specific. Using the following wiki markup:

{noformat}
*Heading*\\
\- Line one\\
\- Another line here\\
\- One more\\
{noformat}

Save the page and then try editing in Rich Text. Select the text and copy/paste further down the page, the output will be...

{noformat}
*Heading*\- Line one\- Another line here\- One more
{noformat}

It seems to be a combination of the escaped bullets (hyphens) and the double slashes at the end of the line. Removing either of those causes the copy/paste function to act normally.

